    "instructions": "Perform the following tasks:\n1. Derive the scaling-critical exponent for a general dissipative PDE with diffusion order 's' in dimension 'n'. Focus on the scaling symmetry of the equation (e.g., $u_\\lambda(x, t) = \\lambda^\\alpha u(\\lambda x, \\lambda^\\beta t)$) to find the critical regularity/exponent.\n2. Express the exponent clearly as a function of $n$ and $s$.\n3. Systematically verify this formula against:\n   - 3D Navier-Stokes (n=3, s=1)\n   - 2D Navier-Stokes (n=2, s=1)\n   - 1D Burgers (n=1, s=1)\n   - Surface Quasi-Geostrophic (SQG) equations (determine $n$ and $s$)\n   - Magnetohydrodynamics (MHD) (determine $n$ and $s$)\n   - Fractional Navier-Stokes (n=3, $s \\in (0,1)$)\n4. Provide a rigorous, step-by-step verification for each case, showing the scaling transformations and the resulting critical values.",
